<% title = "Nutrition for Women | Women's Health Hub"%>

<div class="container py-5">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-lg-8">
      <h1 class="mb-4">Nutrition for Women's Health</h1>
      <p class="lead mb-4">
        Proper nutrition is a cornerstone of women's health throughout the
        lifespan. Discover how to nourish your body with foods that support
        hormonal balance, bone health, energy levels, and overall wellbeing.
      </p>

      <div class="card mb-4">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title">Essential Nutrients for Women</h5>

          <div class="row mb-4">
            <div class="col-md-6">
              <div class="d-flex mb-3">
                <div class="flex-shrink-0 me-3">
                  <div
                    class="bg-primary text-white rounded-circle d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center"
                    style="width: 50px; height: 50px"
                  >
                    <i class="fas fa-bone fa-lg"></i>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div>
                  <h6>Calcium</h6>
                  <p class="mb-0">
                    Essential for bone health, especially important for women
                    due to higher risk of osteoporosis after menopause.
                  </p>
                  <p class="small text-muted mb-0">
                    <strong>Sources:</strong> Dairy products, fortified plant
                    milks, leafy greens, sardines, tofu
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="col-md-6">
              <div class="d-flex mb-3">
                <div class="flex-shrink-0 me-3">
                  <div
                    class="bg-primary text-white rounded-circle d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center"
                    style="width: 50px; height: 50px"
                  >
                    <i class="fas fa-sun fa-lg"></i>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div>
                  <h6>Vitamin D</h6>
                  <p class="mb-0">
                    Works with calcium for bone health, supports immune
                    function, and may help regulate mood.
                  </p>
                  <p class="small text-muted mb-0">
                    <strong>Sources:</strong> Sunlight, fatty fish, fortified
                    foods, egg yolks
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="row mb-4">
            <div class="col-md-6">
              <div class="d-flex mb-3">
                <div class="flex-shrink-0 me-3">
                  <div
                    class="bg-primary text-white rounded-circle d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center"
                    style="width: 50px; height: 50px"
                  >
                    <i class="fas fa-tint fa-lg"></i>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div>
                  <h6>Iron</h6>
                  <p class="mb-0">
                    Crucial for women due to monthly blood loss during
                    menstruation; prevents anemia and fatigue.
                  </p>
                  <p class="small text-muted mb-0">
                    <strong>Sources:</strong> Red meat, poultry, fish, beans,
                    leafy greens, fortified cereals
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="col-md-6">
              <div class="d-flex mb-3">
                <div class="flex-shrink-0 me-3">
                  <div
                    class="bg-primary text-white rounded-circle d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center"
                    style="width: 50px; height: 50px"
                  >
                    <i class="fas fa-dna fa-lg"></i>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div>
                  <h6>Folate (Vitamin B9)</h6>
                  <p class="mb-0">
                    Critical before and during pregnancy to prevent neural tube
                    defects; supports cell function and tissue growth.
                  </p>
                  <p class="small text-muted mb-0">
                    <strong>Sources:</strong> Leafy greens, legumes, citrus
                    fruits, avocados, fortified grains
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="row mb-4">
            <div class="col-md-6">
              <div class="d-flex mb-3">
                <div class="flex-shrink-0 me-3">
                  <div
                    class="bg-primary text-white rounded-circle d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center"
                    style="width: 50px; height: 50px"
                  >
                    <i class="fas fa-fish fa-lg"></i>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div>
                  <h6>Omega-3 Fatty Acids</h6>
                  <p class="mb-0">
                    Support heart health, reduce inflammation, and may help with
                    menstrual pain and mood regulation.
                  </p>
                  <p class="small text-muted mb-0">
                    <strong>Sources:</strong> Fatty fish, flaxseeds, chia seeds,
                    walnuts, algae oil
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="col-md-6">
              <div class="d-flex mb-3">
                <div class="flex-shrink-0 me-3">
                  <div
                    class="bg-primary text-white rounded-circle d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center"
                    style="width: 50px; height: 50px"
                  >
                    <i class="fas fa-capsules fa-lg"></i>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div>
                  <h6>Magnesium</h6>
                  <p class="mb-0">
                    May help reduce PMS symptoms, supports bone health, aids
                    sleep, and regulates muscle and nerve function.
                  </p>
                  <p class="small text-muted mb-0">
                    <strong>Sources:</strong> Nuts, seeds, legumes, leafy
                    greens, whole grains, dark chocolate
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="alert alert-info">
            <i class="fas fa-lightbulb me-2"></i>
            <strong>Did you know?</strong> Women need different amounts of
            certain nutrients throughout their lives. Requirements change during
            puberty, pregnancy, breastfeeding, and menopause.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card mb-4">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title">Nutrition Through Life Stages</h5>

          <div class="accordion" id="nutritionAccordion">
            <div class="accordion-item">
              <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingYoungAdult">
                <button
                  class="accordion-button"
                  type="button"
                  data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                  data-bs-target="#collapseYoungAdult"
                  aria-expanded="true"
                  aria-controls="collapseYoungAdult"
                >
                  <i class="fas fa-venus me-2 text-primary"></i> Young Adulthood
                  (18-35)
                </button>
              </h2>
              <div
                id="collapseYoungAdult"
                class="accordion-collapse collapse show"
                aria-labelledby="headingYoungAdult"
                data-bs-parent="#nutritionAccordion"
              >
                <div class="accordion-body">
                  <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-md-7">
                      <p>
                        This is a critical time to establish healthy eating
                        patterns while also balancing busy lifestyles. Focus on:
                      </p>

                      <h6 class="mt-3">Key Nutritional Needs:</h6>
                      <ul>
                        <li>
                          <strong>Iron:</strong> Particularly important for
                          menstruating women
                        </li>
                        <li>
                          <strong>Calcium and Vitamin D:</strong> To build peak
                          bone mass
                        </li>
                        <li>
                          <strong>Folate:</strong> Essential if planning
                          pregnancy, even in the near future
                        </li>
                        <li>
                          <strong>B Vitamins:</strong> For energy and stress
                          management
                        </li>
                      </ul>

                      <h6 class="mt-3">Eating Strategies:</h6>
                      <ul>
                        <li>Develop meal planning and cooking skills</li>
                        <li>
                          Learn to read food labels and make informed choices
                        </li>
                        <li>Balance social dining with nutritious options</li>
                        <li>Stay hydrated, especially if physically active</li>
                      </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-md-5">
                      <div class="card h-100">
                        <div class="card-body">
                          <h6 class="card-title">Sample Daily Plan</h6>
                          <ul class="list-group list-group-flush">
                            <li class="list-group-item">
                              <strong>Breakfast:</strong> Greek yogurt with
                              berries and nuts
                            </li>
                            <li class="list-group-item">
                              <strong>Lunch:</strong> Spinach salad with grilled
                              chicken, veggies, and quinoa
                            </li>
                            <li class="list-group-item">
                              <strong>Snack:</strong> Apple with almond butter
                            </li>
                            <li class="list-group-item">
                              <strong>Dinner:</strong> Salmon with roasted
                              vegetables and brown rice
                            </li>
                            <li class="list-group-item">
                              <strong>Snack:</strong> Dark chocolate and herbal
                              tea
                            </li>
                          </ul>
                        </div>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="accordion-item">
              <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingPregnancy">
                <button
                  class="accordion-button collapsed"
                  type="button"
                  data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                  data-bs-target="#collapsePregnancy"
                  aria-expanded="false"
                  aria-controls="collapsePregnancy"
                >
                  <i class="fas fa-baby-carriage me-2 text-primary"></i>
                  Pregnancy & Breastfeeding
                </button>
              </h2>
              <div
                id="collapsePregnancy"
                class="accordion-collapse collapse"
                aria-labelledby="headingPregnancy"
                data-bs-parent="#nutritionAccordion"
              >
                <div class="accordion-body">
                  <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-md-7">
                      <p>
                        Nutritional needs increase significantly during
                        pregnancy and breastfeeding. The foods you eat nourish
                        both you and your baby.
                      </p>

                      <h6 class="mt-3">Key Nutritional Needs:</h6>
                      <ul>
                        <li>
                          <strong>Folate/Folic Acid:</strong> Critical in the
                          first trimester to prevent neural tube defects
                        </li>
                        <li>
                          <strong>Iron:</strong> Needs almost double during
                          pregnancy
                        </li>
                        <li>
                          <strong>Calcium:</strong> Supports developing bones
                          and teeth
                        </li>
                        <li>
                          <strong>Protein:</strong> Important for baby's growth
                          and maternal tissue
                        </li>
                        <li>
                          <strong>DHA (Omega-3):</strong> Supports baby's brain
                          and eye development
                        </li>
                      </ul>

                      <p>
                        <strong>During Breastfeeding:</strong> Calorie needs
                        increase even more than during pregnancy. Focus on
                        nutrient-dense foods and staying well-hydrated.
                      </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-md-5">
                      <div class="alert alert-warning mb-3">
                        <i class="fas fa-exclamation-triangle me-2"></i>
                        <strong>Foods to Avoid:</strong>
                        <ul class="mb-0">
                          <li>Raw or undercooked animal products</li>
                          <li>High-mercury fish</li>
                          <li>Unpasteurized dairy</li>
                          <li>Excessive caffeine</li>
                          <li>Alcohol</li>
                        </ul>
                      </div>
                      <div class="alert alert-info">
                        <i class="fas fa-info-circle me-2"></i>
                        <strong>Tip:</strong> A prenatal vitamin is recommended
                        in addition to a healthy diet, not as a replacement for
                        it.
                      </div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="accordion-item">
              <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingPerimen">
                <button
                  class="accordion-button collapsed"
                  type="button"
                  data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                  data-bs-target="#collapsePerimen"
                  aria-expanded="false"
                  aria-controls="collapsePerimen"
                >
                  <i class="fas fa-fire me-2 text-primary"></i> Perimenopause &
                  Menopause
                </button>
              </h2>
              <div
                id="collapsePerimen"
                class="accordion-collapse collapse"
                aria-labelledby="headingPerimen"
                data-bs-parent="#nutritionAccordion"
              >
                <div class="accordion-body">
                  <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-md-7">
                      <p>
                        Hormonal changes during this transition can affect
                        metabolism, bone density, heart health, and body
                        composition. Nutrition plays a key role in managing
                        symptoms and preventing long-term health issues.
                      </p>

                      <h6 class="mt-3">Key Nutritional Focuses:</h6>
                      <ul>
                        <li>
                          <strong>Calcium and Vitamin D:</strong> More critical
                          than ever for bone health
                        </li>
                        <li>
                          <strong>Phytoestrogens:</strong> Plant compounds that
                          may help balance hormones (soy, flaxseed)
                        </li>
                        <li>
                          <strong>Fiber:</strong> Supports heart health and
                          helps manage weight changes
                        </li>
                        <li>
                          <strong>Antioxidants:</strong> Help manage
                          inflammation and support cellular health
                        </li>
                        <li>
                          <strong>Omega-3 Fatty Acids:</strong> May help with
                          mood changes and support heart health
                        </li>
                      </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-md-5">
                      <div class="card h-100">
                        <div class="card-body">
                          <h6 class="card-title">Dietary Strategies</h6>
                          <ul class="list-group list-group-flush">
                            <li class="list-group-item">
                              Adjust calorie intake to match changing metabolism
                            </li>
                            <li class="list-group-item">
                              Stay well-hydrated to help with hot flashes
                            </li>
                            <li class="list-group-item">
                              Limit alcohol, caffeine, and spicy foods that may
                              trigger hot flashes
                            </li>
                            <li class="list-group-item">
                              Include plant-based proteins like soy, legumes,
                              and seeds
                            </li>
                            <li class="list-group-item">
                              Focus on nutrient density rather than calorie
                              restriction
                            </li>
                          </ul>
                        </div>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="accordion-item">
              <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingOlderAdult">
                <button
                  class="accordion-button collapsed"
                  type="button"
                  data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                  data-bs-target="#collapseOlderAdult"
                  aria-expanded="false"
                  aria-controls="collapseOlderAdult"
                >
                  <i class="fas fa-heart me-2 text-primary"></i> Older Adulthood
                  (65+)
                </button>
              </h2>
              <div
                id="collapseOlderAdult"
                class="accordion-collapse collapse"
                aria-labelledby="headingOlderAdult"
                data-bs-parent="#nutritionAccordion"
              >
                <div class="accordion-body">
                  <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-md-7">
                      <p>
                        As women age, calorie needs typically decrease while
                        nutrient needs remain high or even increase. Special
                        attention is needed to maintain muscle mass, bone
                        health, and cognitive function.
                      </p>

                      <h6 class="mt-3">Key Nutritional Focuses:</h6>
                      <ul>
                        <li>
                          <strong>Protein:</strong> Critical for preserving
                          muscle mass; needs often increase
                        </li>
                        <li>
                          <strong>Vitamin B12:</strong> Absorption decreases
                          with age
                        </li>
                        <li>
                          <strong>Calcium and Vitamin D:</strong> Continue to be
                          important for bone health
                        </li>
                        <li>
                          <strong>Fiber:</strong> Helps with digestive changes
                          that come with aging
                        </li>
                        <li>
                          <strong>Hydration:</strong> Sense of thirst diminishes
                          with age
                        </li>
                      </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-md-5">
                      <div class="alert alert-success h-100">
                        <h6>
                          <i class="fas fa-check-circle me-2"></i> Focus on
                          these foods:
                        </h6>
                        <ul>
                          <li>Colorful fruits and vegetables (antioxidants)</li>
                          <li>Fatty fish and nuts (brain health)</li>
                          <li>
                            High-quality protein sources (muscle maintenance)
                          </li>
                          <li>Whole grains and legumes (steady energy)</li>
                          <li>Probiotic foods like yogurt (gut health)</li>
                        </ul>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card mb-4">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title">
            Nutrition for Common Women's Health Concerns
          </h5>

          <div class="table-responsive">
            <table class="table table-hover">
              <thead>
                <tr>
                  <th>Health Concern</th>
                  <th>Nutritional Approach</th>
                  <th>Foods to Include</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr>
                  <td><strong>PMS</strong></td>
                  <td>
                    <ul>
                      <li>Limit salt, caffeine, alcohol</li>
                      <li>Regular, balanced meals</li>
                      <li>Focus on calcium, magnesium, vitamin B6</li>
                    </ul>
                  </td>
                  <td>
                    <ul>
                      <li>Leafy greens, yogurt, seeds</li>
                      <li>Whole grains</li>
                      <li>Small, frequent protein sources</li>
                    </ul>
                  </td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td>
                    <strong>PCOS</strong><br /><small
                      >(Polycystic Ovary Syndrome)</small
                    >
                  </td>
                  <td>
                    <ul>
                      <li>Focus on low glycemic index foods</li>
                      <li>Moderate carbohydrate intake</li>
                      <li>Include anti-inflammatory foods</li>
                    </ul>
                  </td>
                  <td>
                    <ul>
                      <li>Non-starchy vegetables</li>
                      <li>Lean proteins</li>
                      <li>Healthy fats</li>
                      <li>Berries, nuts, fatty fish</li>
                    </ul>
                  </td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td><strong>Endometriosis</strong></td>
                  <td>
                    <ul>
                      <li>Anti-inflammatory approach</li>
                      <li>Minimize processed foods</li>
                      <li>Consider limiting gluten and dairy</li>
                    </ul>
                  </td>
                  <td>
                    <ul>
                      <li>Fatty fish, olive oil</li>
                      <li>Colorful fruits and vegetables</li>
                      <li>Turmeric, ginger</li>
                      <li>Legumes, nuts, seeds</li>
                    </ul>
                  </td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td><strong>Osteoporosis</strong></td>
                  <td>
                    <ul>
                      <li>Calcium-rich diet</li>
                      <li>Adequate vitamin D</li>
                      <li>Vitamin K and magnesium</li>
                      <li>Weight-bearing exercise complements nutrition</li>
                    </ul>
                  </td>
                  <td>
                    <ul>
                      <li>Dairy or fortified alternatives</li>
                      <li>Leafy greens</li>
                      <li>Salmon with bones</li>
                      <li>Nuts and seeds</li>
                    </ul>
                  </td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td><strong>Thyroid Issues</strong></td>
                  <td>
                    <ul>
                      <li>Iodine balance (not too much, not too little)</li>
                      <li>Selenium-rich foods</li>
                      <li>Consider limiting goitrogenic foods</li>
                    </ul>
                  </td>
                  <td>
                    <ul>
                      <li>Seafood, iodized salt</li>
                      <li>Brazil nuts, fish, eggs</li>
                      <li>Cook cruciferous vegetables if sensitive</li>
                    </ul>
                  </td>
                </tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>

          <div class="alert alert-warning mt-3">
            <i class="fas fa-exclamation-triangle me-2"></i>
            <strong>Important:</strong> These are general guidelines. Always
            consult with your healthcare provider about nutritional approaches
            for specific health conditions, especially before making significant
            dietary changes.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title">Building a Balanced Plate</h5>

          <p>
            A balanced approach to eating can help ensure you get the nutrients
            you need while maintaining a healthy weight and energy levels.
          </p>

          <div class="row mb-4">
            <div class="col-md-6">
              <h6>
                <i class="fas fa-check-circle text-success me-2"></i> What to
                Include:
              </h6>
              <ul>
                <li>
                  <strong>Vegetables:</strong> Fill half your plate with
                  colorful vegetables
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Fruits:</strong> Include a variety of whole fruits
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Whole Grains:</strong> Choose brown rice, quinoa,
                  oats, whole wheat
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Lean Proteins:</strong> Fish, poultry, beans, tofu,
                  nuts, eggs
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Healthy Fats:</strong> Avocados, olive oil, nuts,
                  seeds
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Dairy or Alternatives:</strong> Choose
                  calcium-fortified options if avoiding dairy
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-6">
              <h6>
                <i class="fas fa-minus-circle text-danger me-2"></i> What to
                Limit:
              </h6>
              <ul>
                <li>
                  <strong>Added Sugars:</strong> Sodas, sweets, many processed
                  foods
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Refined Grains:</strong> White bread, white rice,
                  pastries
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Processed Meats:</strong> Bacon, sausage, deli meats
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Excess Sodium:</strong> Packaged foods, restaurant
                  meals
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Trans Fats:</strong> Fried foods, some packaged baked
                  goods
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Alcohol:</strong> If consumed, limit to moderate
                  amounts
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="alert alert-success">
            <div class="row align-items-center">
              <div class="col-md-9">
                <h5 class="alert-heading">The Mediterranean Diet</h5>
                <p>
                  This eating pattern is often recommended for women's health
                  because it's rich in nutrients that support hormonal health,
                  heart health, brain function, and longevity. It emphasizes:
                </p>
                <ul class="mb-0">
                  <li>
                    Abundant plant foods (fruits, vegetables, whole grains,
                    legumes, nuts)
                  </li>
                  <li>Olive oil as the primary fat source</li>
                  <li>Moderate amounts of fish, poultry, eggs, and dairy</li>
                  <li>Limited red meat</li>
                  <li>
                    Optional moderate red wine consumption (if appropriate)
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div class="col-md-3 text-center">
                <i class="fas fa-utensils fa-4x text-success opacity-75"></i>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="col-lg-4 mt-4 mt-lg-0">
      <div class="card mb-4">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title">Nutrition Tips & Strategies</h5>

          <div class="d-flex align-items-center mb-3">
            <div class="flex-shrink-0 me-3">
              <div
                class="bg-primary text-white rounded-circle d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center"
                style="width: 50px; height: 50px"
              >
                <i class="fas fa-clock fa-lg"></i>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h6 class="mb-0">Meal Planning</h6>
              <p class="small mb-0">
                Set aside time each week to plan meals, create a shopping list,
                and prep ingredients to make healthy eating easier during busy
                days.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="d-flex align-items-center mb-3">
            <div class="flex-shrink-0 me-3">
              <div
                class="bg-primary text-white rounded-circle d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center"
                style="width: 50px; height: 50px"
              >
                <i class="fas fa-tint fa-lg"></i>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h6 class="mb-0">Stay Hydrated</h6>
              <p class="small mb-0">
                Aim for at least 8-10 cups of fluids daily. Water should be your
                primary beverage, with herbal teas and infused water as
                flavorful alternatives.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="d-flex align-items-center mb-3">
            <div class="flex-shrink-0 me-3">
              <div
                class="bg-primary text-white rounded-circle d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center"
                style="width: 50px; height: 50px"
              >
                <i class="fas fa-shopping-basket fa-lg"></i>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h6 class="mb-0">Grocery Shopping</h6>
              <p class="small mb-0">
                Shop the perimeter of the store first, where fresh foods are
                usually located. Read labels and choose items with shorter
                ingredient lists.
